text: Propoxate (INN; R7464) is a never marketed anesthetic related to etomidate and metomidate. Although not employed in the treatment of humans, it has been used as an anesthetic in fish. ==References== Category:Ethyl esters Category:GABAA receptor positive allosteric modulators Category:General anesthetics Category:Imidazoles Category:Janssen Pharmaceutica
title: Propoxate
